.TH "compute_mps_bg_map" 9 "compute_mps_bg_map" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
compute_mps_bg_map \- compute the MPS Buffer Group Map for a Port
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" compute_mps_bg_map
.BI "(struct adapter *adapter "  ","
.BI "int pidx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adapter" 12
the adapter
.IP "pidx" 12
the port index

Computes and returns a bitmap indicating which MPS buffer groups are
associated with the given Port.  Bit i is set if buffer group i is
used by the Port.
